acters%20in%20the%20infamous%20incident%20that%20inspired%20Herman%20Melville's%201851%20novel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs-reading-list-favorite-books-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BMoby-Dick.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoby-Dick%26quot%3B%20is%20inspired%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhales-taught-each-other-how-to-avoid-harpoons-19th-century-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esperm%20whale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20a%20killer%20whale%2C%20sinking%20the%20whaling%20boat%20%26quot%3BEssex%26quot%3B%20in%201820.%20But%20what%20happened%20after%20the%20sinking%3F%20That%20story%20isn't%20as%20well-known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Nathaniel%20Philbrick's%20book%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Heart%20of%20the%20Sea%3A%20The%20Tragedy%20of%20the%20Whaleship%20Essex%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20crew%20of%20the%20sinking%20ship%20escaped%20to%20lifeboats.%20But%20their%20troubles%20had%20just%20begun.%20Killer%20whales%20later%20attempted%20to%20sink%20one%20of%20the%20small%20boats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FEssex-whaling-ship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20said%20the%20sailors%20were%20unsure%20what%20kind%20of%20animal%20attacked%20the%20lifeboat.%20It%20could%20have%20been%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaptive-orcas-seaworld-should-they-be-released-sea-pen-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorca%20%3C%2Fa%3Eor%20some%20other%20large%20marine%20animal.%20But%20the%20story%20sounds%20eerily%20similar%20to%20the%20orcas%20that%20have%20been%20ripping%20off%20boat%20rudders%20in%20the%20Strait%20of%20Gibraltar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhilbrick's%20book%20went%20on%20to%20win%20the%20National%20Book%20Award%20for%20nonfiction%20in%202000%20and%20was%20adapted%20into%20a%202015%20%3Ca%20