0County%2C%20ruled%20last%20week%20that%20the%20plaintiff%20in%20a%20product%20liability%20lawsuit%20against%20Tesla%20could%20proceed%20to%20trial%20and%20bring%20punitive%20damages%20claims%20against%20the%20company%20for%20intentional%20misconduct%20and%20gross%20negligence.%20The%20order%20has%20not%20been%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20is%20a%20setback%20for%20Tesla%20after%20the%20company%20won%20two%20product%20liability%20trials%20in%20California%20earlier%20this%20year%20over%20the%20Autopilot%20driver%20assistant%20system.%20A%20Tesla%20spokesperson%20could%20not%20immediately%20be%20reached%20for%20comment%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Florida%20lawsuit%20arose%20out%20of%20a%202019%20crash%20north%20of%20Miami%20in%20which%20owner%20Stephen%20Banner's%20Model%203%20drove%20under%20the%20trailer%20of%20an%2018-wheeler%20big%20rig%20truck%20that%20had%20turned%20onto%20the%20road%2C%20shearing%20off%20the%20Tesla's%20roof%20and%20killing%20Banner.%20A%20trial%20set%20for%20October%20was%20delayed%2C%20and%20has%20not%20been%20rescheduled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScott%20found%20that%20the%20plaintiff%2C%20Banner's%20wife%2C%20should%20be%20able%20to%20argue%20to%20jurors%20that%20Tesla's%20warnings%20in%20its%20manuals%20and%20%26quot%3Bclickwrap%26quot%3B%20agreement%20were%20inadequate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20said%20the%20accident%20is%20%26quot%3Beerily%20similar%26quot%3B%20to%20a%202016%20fatal%20crash%20involving%20Joshua%20Brown%20in%20which%20the%20Autopilot%20system%20failed%20to%20detect%20crossing%20trucks%2C%20leading%20vehicles%20to%20go%20underneath%20a%20tractor%20trailer%20at%20high%20speeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20reasonable%20to%20conclude%20that%20the%20Defendant%20Tesla%20through%20its%20CEO%20and%20engineers%20was%20acutely%20aware%20of%20the%20problem%20with%20the%20'Autopilot'%20failing%20to%20detect%20cross%20traffic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3