by%20more%20and%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20as%20though%20books%20sitting%20on%20their%20shelves%20are%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20can%20you%20say%20you%20have%20a%20corner%20on%20the%20truth%3F%20Look%20at%20the%20multiplicity%20of%20thoughts%20and%20diversity%20of%20perspectives%20we%20represent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0Books%2C%20naturally%2C%20make%20one%20think%2C%20reason%2C%20imagine%2C%20and%20question.%20Little%20wonder%20that%20authoritarian%20regimes%20feel%20threatened%20by%20libraries%20(a%20case%20in%20point%20being%20the%20continued%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Fstudents-claim-move-to-shut-history-centre-library-at-jnu%2Farticleshow%2F102407604.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edefunding%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20libraries%20in%20public%20universities%2C%20such%20as%20the%20ones%20at%20JNU.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EImagine%2C%20then%2C%20the%20unexpected%20shock%20of%20encountering%20a%20bigot%20in%20a%20library!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20many%20years%20now%2C%20I%20have%20been%20conducting%20workshops%20for%20high%20school%20students%20on%20topics%20like%20emotional%20intelligence%2C%20empathy%2C%20and%20the%20dangers%20of%20bullying.%20Many%20of%20these%20workshops%20end%20up%20being%20conducted%20in%20school%20libraries%2C%20because%20these%20are%20the%20only%20spaces%20many%20schools%20have%20available%20for%20such%20programmes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20too%20long%20ago%2C%20after%20finishing%20a%20workshop%20on%20the%20topic%20of%20empathy%20and%20kindness%20for%2010%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20graders%20(in%20a%20school%20library)%2C%20I%20was%20packing%20up%20my%20laptop%20when%20the%20very%20pleasant%20and%20cheerful%20library%20assistant%20mentioned%20how%20important%20it%20is%20to%20have%20such%20conversations%20with%20teenagers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20concurred%2C%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20hate-filled%20environment%20these%20kids%20are%20growing%20up%20in.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20we%20chatted%20a%20bit%20more%20about%20how%20polarised%20society%20is%2C%20the%20lady%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%2C%20if%20only%20Muslims%20were%20eradicated%20from%20the%20world%2C%20all%20our%20problems%20would%20be%20solved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20must%20have%20been%20my%20shell-shocked%20expression%20that%20stopped%20her%20mid-sentence.%20With%20a%20sudden%20note%20of%20alarm%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAre%20you%20a%20Muslim%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20bit%20late%20to%20ask%20me%20that%20now%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20it%3F%E2%80%9D%20I%20responded.%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAap%20school%20me%20baithke%20yeh%20keh%20rahe%20hain%3F%20Aur%20vo%20bhi%20library%20may%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%20(You%20said%20that%20sitting%20in%20a%20school%20and%20that%20too%2C%20in%20a%20library%3F)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESlightly%20flustered%2C%20the%20lady%20responded%2C%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20true%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20it%3F%20Look%20back%20at%20Indian%20history.%20All%20terrorists%20have%20always%20been%20Muslims%2C%20haven%E2%80%99t%20they%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETrying%20to%20keep%20my%20voice%20steady%20(for%20this%20sort%20of%20bigotry%20never%20fails%20to%20startle)%2C%20I%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20Muslim%20who%20killed%20Gandhi%2C%20was%20it%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNo%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20true%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20have%20Muslims%20done%20to%20you%20personally%20that%20you%20hate%20them%20so%20much%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20hate%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20that%20is%20the%20image%20that%20is%20created%20of%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20you%20are%20letting%20someone%20else%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20become%20your%20reality!%E2%80%9D%20I%20said%2C%20making%20a%20massive%20effort%20to%20stay%20calm.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20are%20living%20in%20a%20country%20whose%20constitution%20honours%20all%20citizens%20equally%2C%20ma%E2%80%99am.%20You%20cannot%20make%20statements%20like%20this%2C%20especially%20not%20in%20a%20school.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20judging%20by%20the%20blank%20and%20uncomprehending%20look%20on%20her%20face%2C%20I%20might%20as%20well%20have%20been%20speaking%20in%20some%20ancient%20and%20unknown%20dialect.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20I%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20library%2C%20I%20remembered%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FJQS-_9K5-Dk%3Fsi%3DpocYAj7L8Fxo9pdU%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Espeech%20I%20had%20seen%20on%20YouTube%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20just%20the%20previous%20evening.%20It%20was%20an%20address%20given%20by%20the%20Israeli%20journalist%2C%20Gideon%20Levy%2C%20in%20Washington%20D.C.%20in%202016.%20In%20it%2C%20he%20had%20said%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20have%20a%20dialogue%20today%20with%20most%20Israelis%2C%20even%20for%20me%2C%20is%20an%20impossible%20job.%20Many%20times%2C%20I%20find%20myself%20(talking%20to)%20ordinary%20Israelis%2C%20good%20people.%20They%20would%20volunteer%20anywhere.%20But%20when%20you%20start%20to%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20the%20Occupation%2C%20after%20two%20minutes%20you%20want%20to%20tear%20your%20hair%20out!%20You%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20to%20do!%20You%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20where%20to%20start!%20The%20brainwashing%20is%20so%20deep%2C%20and%20the%20denial%20is%20so%20deep!%20And%20the%20ignorance!%20They%20know%20nothing!%20Anyone%20in%20this%20hall%20knows%20so%20much%20more%20about%20the%20Occupation%20than%20the%20average%20Israelis%20(who)%20know%20nothing%2C%20and%20what%20they%20know%20is%20wrong!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELevy%20might%20as%20well%20have%20been%20talking%20about%20the%20average%20mainstream-media-nourished%20Indian%2C%20a%20prime%20example%20of%20whom%20I%20had%20just%20encountered.%20The%20most%20disturbing%20facet%20of%20the%20conversation%20with%20this%20lady%20was%20how%20pleasantly%20earnest%20she%20was%20in%20her%20bigotry.%20There%20was%20no%20anger%2C%20no%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ead-hominem%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20attack%2C%20just%20a%20very%20sincere%20belief%20that%20an%20entire%20community%20of%20Indians%20is%20intrinsically%20evil.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhatever%20else%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20legacy%20might%20be%2C%20it%20will%20most%20certainly%20include%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20entire%20sub-stratum%20of%20society%20that%2C%20under%20his%20watch%2C%20genuinely%20believed%20that%20a%20whole%20community%20in%20India%20was%20fundamentally%20bad.%20This%20ecosystem%20was%20nurtured%20by%20a%20steady%20injection%20of%20hate%20and%20misinformation%2C%20not%20unlike%20the%20drip%20irrigation%20methods%20that%20desert%20nations%20often%20employ.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20damage%20that%20has%20been%20done%20to%20the%20minds%20and%20hearts%20of%20millions%20over%20the%20last%20ten%20years%20is%20deep.%20It%20will%20take%20time%20to%20heal%2C%20recover%20and%20rebuild.%20One%20hopes%20and%20prays%20that%20the%20results%20of%20the%20elections%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20(both%20at%20the%20state%20and%20at%20the%20national%20level)%20will%20create%20an%20opportunity%20for%20facts%20and%20empathy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20antidotes%20to%20misinformation%20and%20bigotry%20%E2%80%93%20to%20somehow%20enter%20the%20national%20discourse%20once%20again%20in%20a%20steady%2C%20sustained%2C%20and%20significant%20manner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20alternative%20is%20too%20horrific%20to%20contemplate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20set%20up%20libraries%20%E2%80%93%20however%20small%20%E2%80%93%20with%20books%20that%20will%20keep%20our%20minds%20and%20hearts%20open%2C%20and%20let%E2%80%99s%20keep%20sharing%20with%20others%20what%20we%20have%20learned%20from%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERohit%20Kumar%20is%20an%20educator%2C%20author%2C%20and%20independent%20journalist%2C%20and%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aletsempathize%40gmail.com%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eletsempathize%40gmail.com%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700568337000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21163929%2Flibrary.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-bigot-in-the-library%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20damage%20that%20has%20been%20done%20to%20the%20minds%20and%20hearts%20of%20millions%20over%20the%20last%20ten%20years%20is%20deep.%20It%20will%20take%20time%20to%20heal%2C%20recover%20and%20rebuild.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-bigot-in-the-library%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Juggling%20Motherhood%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%201st%20MasterChef%20Contestant%20Overcame%20Failure%20to%20Create%20History%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDr%20Rukhsaar%20Sayeed%20cooked%20for%20the%20first%20time%20when%20she%20was%2012.%20Hailing%20from%20Tangmarg%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325808%2Fkashmir-daily-wager-umer-ahmad-ganie-cracked-neet-exam-without-coaching-break-poverty%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20was%20visiting%20her%20father%20in%20Saudi%20during%20her%20winter%20vacations.%20Bored%2C%20she%20whipped%20up%20a%20caramel%20custard%2C%20which%20her%20family%20loved.%20This%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20now-34-year-old%E2%80%99s%20culinary%20journey%20and%20her%20dream%20of%20being%20a%20chef.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Rukhsaar%20was%20growing%20up%20in%20the%2090s%2C%20she%20did%20not%20have%20proper%20guidance%20to%20achieve%20her%20goal%20of%20becoming%20a%20chef.%20Without%20internet%20access%2C%20information%20or%20career%20counselling%2C%20she%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20which%20path%20to%20pursue.%20So%20she%20took%20up%20food%20technology%2C%20a%20newly%20introduced%20course%20at%20her%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20her%20surprise%2C%20food%20technology%20was%20a%20completely%20different%20ball%20game%20%E2%80%94%20it%20did%20not%20involve%20cooking%20at%20all!%20However%2C%20she%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98new%20world%E2%80%99%20she%20was%20introduced%20to%20and%20went%20on%20to%20pursue%20a%20BTech%2C%20MTech%20and%20PhD%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20enjoyed%20learning%20biochemistry%2C%20preservation%2C%20processing%2C%20and%20research%20of%20food%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20her%20education%2C%20the%20food%20technologist%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20choose%20a%20job%20of%20her%20liking%2C%20but%20here%E2%80%99s%20where%20her%20other%20dream%20kicks%20in%20%E2%80%94%20to%20be%20her%20own%20boss.%20And%20she%20was%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20the%20work%20and%20wait%20for%20her%20chance%20in%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20chance%20presented%20itself%20even%20before%20the%20entrepreneur%20completed%20her%20PhD%2C%20and%20led%20to%20the%20launch%20of%20her%20food%20venture%20%E2%80%98Khalis%20Foods%E2%80%99.%20Today%2C%20Rukhsaar%20has%20managed%20t