ity%20over%20its%20new%20cold-war%20rival%20and%20the%20liberal%20order%2C%20which%20has%20already%20been%20under%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuest%20for%20alternatives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20powers%20in%20an%20emerging%20multipolar%20world%20argue%20that%20it%20is%20too%20West-centric%20and%20lacks%20diversity%20and%20accountability.%20Global%20South%20groupings%20like%20BRICS%20are%20seen%20as%20budding%20platforms%20prepping%20for%20an%20alternative%20alignment%20of%20power%20with%20a%20different%20set%20of%20rules%20of%20engagement.%20Might%20Gaza%20hasten%20the%20process%3F%20Could%20the%20liberal%20order%20survive%20the%20single%20greatest%20instance%20of%20its%20delegitimization%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20may%20be%20trying%20times%20for%20the%20liberal%20order%2C%20which%20is%20bad%20news%20at%20a%20time%20of%20a%20worldwide%20rise%20of%20right-wing%20authoritarians%20peddling%20toxic%20nationalism.%20But%20it%20may%20still%20not%20be%20the%20end%20of%20days%20for%20it.%20The%20Global%20South%20is%20hardly%20a%20homogenous%20entity.%20Sample%20the%20difference%20between%20India%E2%80%99s%20strong%20backing%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20pro-Palestine%20stance%20of%20other%20BRICS%20founding%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholars%20of%20international%20order%20such%20as%20John%20Ikenberry%20have%20long%20argued%20that%C2%A0the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F0305829810366477%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20liberal%20hegemonic%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0may%20be%20in%20crisis%2C%C2%A0but%20not%20the%20liberal%20order%20itself%20as%20there%20is%20no%C2%A0grand%20alternative%20to%20it%2C%20and%20as%20American%20unipolarity%20fades%20and%20other%20powers%20emerge%2C%20there%20will%20appear%20new%20international%20leaders%20happy%20to%20engage%20with%2C%20and%20own%2C%20the%20liberal%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20emerging%20and%20middle%20powers%20such%20as%20China%2C%20India%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20Turkey%2C%20while%20wanting%20to%20imbue%20global%20governing%20institutions%20with%20what%20they%20consider%20their%20own%20national%20values%20and%20interests%2C%20have%20also%20engaged%20actively%20with%20the%20rules-based%20order%2C%20not%20rejected%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20rules-based%20order%20won%E2%80%99t%20die%20from%20the%20wounds%20of%20Gaza%20even%20as%20its%20moral%20failure%20makes%20it%20more%20vulnerable%20than%20ever%20before%20to%20demands%20for%20change.%20But%20Gaza%20could%20well%20mark%20that%20moment%20of%20transition%20when%20it%20ceases%20to%20be%20the%20preserve%20of%20an%20America%20seen%20to%20be%20too%20partisan%20or%20too%20powerless%20to%20mediate%20the%20rules%20fairly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moment%20of%20transition%20that%20marks%20America%E2%80%99s%20passing%20as%20the%20dominant%20global%20power%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20Whatever%20form%20it%20takes%20after%20it%20emerges%20from%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20rubble%2C%20the%20liberal%20order%20will%20not%20be%20America%E2%80%99s%20to%20wield%20any%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdebasish-roy-chowdhury%5C%22%3EDebasish%20Roy%20Chowdhury%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20based%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22italic%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasiatimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2Fthe-rubble-of-americas-rules-based-order-in-gaza%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20republished%20with%20permission%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasiatimes.com%2F%5C%22%3EAsia%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700560814000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F22120200%2FFmydWD-WQAIX5hb.jpeg%22%2C%22orig